<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Robotics Field Service Engineer - James Campbell"
	heroImage="/hero-bg.png"
>
	<p>
		I am a Robotics Field Service Engineer with a B.S. in Computer Engineering and over 20 years of experience specializing in the deployment, commissioning, and on-site maintenance of autonomous systems. Throughout my career, I have developed a deep expertise in hardware diagnostics, component-level repair, and electrical troubleshooting for mission-critical robotics and automotive platforms.
	</p>

	<p>
		My core strengths lie in field operations and deployment. I have a proven track record of leading international field operations, performing comprehensive site surveys, and managing complex system bring-ups. Whether I am conducting site and factory acceptance testing (SAT/FAT) or executing preventive maintenance and failure recovery, my goal is always to ensure maximum uptime in the most demanding environments.
	</p>

	<p>
		I possess deep technical proficiency across multiple hardware disciplines. I am highly skilled in utilizing diagnostic tools like oscilloscopes and logic analyzers for component-level prototyping, PCB trace repair, and JTAG/SWD debugging. My experience extends to complex electromechanical systems, including DC motor control, SLAM-based navigation hardware, and the integration and calibration of LIDAR, GPS, RF, and environmental sensors.
	</p>

	<p>
		Furthermore, I bring robust expertise in industrial communication and field networking. I regularly diagnose and validate CAN Bus (J1939, CANopen), RS-232/485, and I2C/SPI interfaces to ensure seamless data flow. Combining this with extensive experience in Linux CLI system monitoring, shell scripting, and TCP/IP networking, I bridge the gap between low-level hardware and distributed system connectivity.
	</p>
</Layout>
